modules.description: Handles image data serialization by providing functions to write PNG and JPEG formats. Operates on raw pixel data stored in arrays and byte buffers. Used to output generated graphics or processed images to files in specific image formats.

Writes image files in PNG, BMP, TGA, and HDR formats from raw pixel data. Accepts width, height, channel count, and buffers of 8-bit unsigned integers or 32-bit floats. Used to save generated textures, render outputs, or image processing results to disk.
